This paper proposes a hybrid machine learning plus ontology-based reasoning system for detecting human psychological artifacts at scale. The use of machine learning and ontology-based reasoning suggests that this paper is likely to belong to the categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the focus on human psychology and organizational performance suggests that this paper may also belong to the categories of Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) and Cybersecurity (cs.CY). Finally, the mention of graph science and model management systems suggests that this paper may also belong to the category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
